    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Shadow pricing can indeed be complex and often involves a degree of educated guesswork, as it requires estimating the value of intangible benefits. If GizmoWorks miscalculates the shadow price, it could lead to a suboptimal decision, but it doesn't necessarily mean their entire long-term strategy is ruined. Companies often have to make decisions with incomplete information and must be prepared to adapt as they learn more. It's like a game of chess; a wrong move doesn't mean you're out of the game, just that you need to adjust your strategy. They might have to pivot and invest more in the marketing campaign if they realize the machinery didn't pay off as expected. It's all about staying agile and responsive to the market.",
      "source": "target",
